<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB04745</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT STRENGTHENING THE OFFICE OF THE GOVERNMENT CORPORATE COUNSEL AND APPROPRIATING FUNDS THEREFOR</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Intends to improve and safeguard the legal interests and services of Government-Owned or Controlled 
Corporations (GOCCs), Government Financial Institutions (GFIs), Government Instrumentalities with 
Corporate Powers (GCIPs), Government Corporate Entities (GCEs) as defined in R.A.No.10149 as well 
as their subsidiaries and corporate offsprings including economic zones, state universities and water
districts.

Aims to address the expanding needs of these government corporations due to the complexities of their
requirements brought by the modern business situations and conditions through proper equipping and
provision of adequate compensation to the officials and employees of OGCC which should be at par with
the salary grades, positions, salaries and benefits of its counterparts in the DOJ performing similar
functions and providing similar legal services.

</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : "Office of the Government Corporate Charter" </td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>OAMINAL, HENRY S.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-09-20</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Nieto (000 2019-12-16)</td><td>2. Dalipe (000 2019-12-16)</td><tr><td>3. Savellano (000 2019-12-16)</td><td>4. Vargas Alfonso (000 2020-03-02)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON JUSTICE ON 2019-09-24</td></tr></table>